Japan must try harder to reduce its tradesurplus or the yen will come under renewed upward pressure,Economic Planning Minister Tetsuo Kondo.    He told a press luncheon he hoped Japan could cut itscurrent account surplus by some 10 billion dlrs a year until itis reduced to some 50 to 60 billion dlrs. In the fiscal yearended March 31 the surplus totalled 93.76 billion dlrs, orabout 4.5 pct of GNP.    The 6,000 billion yen economic stimulation package thegovernment unveiled late last month would help slash Japan'scurrent account surplus by five to six billion dlrs, he said. REUTER&#3;